weird, but there are not too many pieces on the board so the king is not going
to be in any danger. However, protecting the e6-pawn and approaching the
center in the event of a possible upcoming endgame seems very reasonable. It
also does not make sense to take on g2 and improve the White's knight on e1.
Please check out the chapter on 2.g3 3.c4 for more detail.} *

