{[#] How should Black continue?} 8... a5 $1 {I really like this positional
move. There are several ideas behind it. First of all, we are preventing any
potential c2-c3 and b2-b4-related ideas. Secondly, we are possibly preparing
stuff like ...b7-b6 or even ...b7-b5! followed by ...Ba6. Now the game is not
forcing by any means, but it's fair enough to say that White is likely to make
moves like Nbd2, c2-c3, maybe Nf3-h4-f5. We will, on the other hand, strive to
play ...Qe7, ...c7-c6, ... possibly ...Rd8 or ...Re8. Maybe the knight will go
to e6 via c5 or via f8. Please see the chapter on 2. g3 3.Bg2 for more detail.}
*

