{[#] What plan am I suggesting here?} 9... Nh5 $1 {We would love the trade,
while if White declines, he will encounter severe dynamic problems.} 10. Bxg7 (
10. d4 $2 c5 11. Nf3 Nc6 $17 {[%csl Rb2,Rc4,Rd4,Re1,Re3,Rf4][%cal Gc5d4,Gd8a5,
Gg7b2,Gh5f4] Black is pressuring the center like crazy and White always needs
to watch out for the weak f4-pawn, as the knight on h5 is doing a fantastic
job. Also, the ...Qa5+ might prove very disruptive and dangerous! White's
already nearly lost.}) 10... Nxg7 11. d4 c6 12. Bg2 Nd7 {We reach another very
solid position, similar to the ones we get in the main line. We might just
continue with ... a7-a5-a4, getting some play on the queenside while
simultaneously taming the g2-bishop. It's equal, but a little more fun for
Black.} *

