{[#] What is Black's key idea here?} 7... Nh6 $1 {While this move might look a
bit ugly, the idea behind it is very cool. The thing is that White wants to go
Be3 to tuck our queen away and to push d3-d4. Once he does that, our knight
lands on f5, creating pressure on both the e3-bishop and the d4-pawn, ending
up on a perfect spot! Please check the 2.c4 d4 3.e3 chapter for further
information.} *

