{[#] What's White's idea here and how should we prepare to meet it?} 10... Qd7
$1 {This is the human move and my suggestion. The thing is that White wants to
play Nb3 and challenge/trade the c5-knight, which is the only defender of the
b7-pawn. So, we prepare to castle in order to protect it.} (10... Nf6 {Moves
like these are fine according to the engine, but I don't like the fact that
after} 11. Nb3 {We either need to play the ugly moves like ...Qc8 or ...Rb8,
or give up a pawn.}) 11. Nb3 O-O-O 12. a4 Nf6 13. a5 e4 $1 {Another key
decision - we shut down the g2-bishop and make all the White queenside play
rather inefficient. Please, do check out the chapter on 2.c4 d4 3.b4! - the
sidelines on move 4.} *

