{[#] A slightly unexpected question - a puzzle from White's perspective! How
should he continue in order not to be worse? Or, let's ask this differently -
what's his best move/plan?} 7. c5 $1 {[%cal Gf1c4]} (7. b5 $6 Nd7 {Black will
just be better as he owns the c5-square and because the b2-bishop is rather
useless and restricted.}) 7... Nf6 8. Bc4 {The bishop, quite surprisingly,
gets developed to c4 instead of g2 and White is doing alright - so do we,
though.} Be7 9. O-O O-O 10. Re1 axb4 11. axb4 Rxa1 12. Bxa1 b6 $1 $11 {Here in
the theoretical chapter on the 2.c4 d4 3.b4 sidelines on move 4 I quote
Khenkin's game, claiming Black is totally fine - do check it out if you need
to refresh this in your memory!} *

